                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d852">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 296/2600: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-08T16:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 8, 1929—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 8—1:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. Reparation 164.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Is the understanding correct that the six Governments, before proceeding to
                    appoint Americans whom they select, will submit their names to the
                    Department?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
